1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 15-10 and a new section to
2 chapter 15.1-09 of the North Dakota Century Code, relating to displays of the ten
3 commandments in state educational institutions and public schools.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 15-10 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
6 and enacted as follows:
7 Ten commandments - Displays.
8 1. The state board of higher education shall display the ten commandments in each
9 classroom on the campus of each state educational institution under its control and
10 administration.
11 2. The display must be:
12 a. On a poster or framed document that is at least eleven inches [27.94
13 centimeters] in width and fourteen inches [35.56 centimeters] in length.
14 b. The central focus of the poster or framed document.
15 c. Printed in a large, easily readable font.
16 3. The text must read as follows:
17 The Ten Commandments
18 I AM the LORD thy God.
19 Thou shalt have no other gods before me.
20 Thou shalt not make to thyself any graven images.
21 Thou shalt not take the Name of the Lord thy God in vain.
22 Remember the Sabbath day, to keep it holy.
23 Honor thy father and thy mother, that thy days may be long upon the land which the
24 Lord thy God giveth thee.
