12 SECTION 2. A new section to chapter 15.1-09 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
13 and enacted as follows:
14 Ten commandments - Displays.
15 1. A board of a school district shall display the ten commandments in each classroom
16 and building on school grounds in the school district.
17 2. The display must be:
18 a. On a poster or framed document that is at least eleven inches [27.94
19 centimeters] in width and fourteen inches [35.56 centimeters] in length.
20 b. The central focus of the poster or framed document.
21 c. Printed in a large, easily readable font.
22 3. The text must read as follows:
23 The Ten Commandments
24 I AM the LORD thy God.
25 Thou shalt have no other gods before me.
26 Thou shalt not make to thyself any graven images.
27 Thou shalt not take the Name of the Lord thy God in vain.
28 Remember the Sabbath day, to keep it holy.
29 Honor thy father and thy mother, that thy days may be long upon the land which the
30 Lord thy God giveth thee.
